title: Australia's Banking System on High Alert: Cybersecurity Risks Surge
description: The Australian Prudential Regulation Authority (APRA) warns of increased cyberattack risks to the country's banking system due to rising geopolitical tensions. APRA plans to intensify its cybersecurity measures, highlighting vulnerabilities in financial institutions. The use of artificial intelligence and recent cyberattack data further underline the growing threats.
content:
Australia's banking system is under increased threat from cyberattacks, according to the Australian Prudential Regulation Authority (APRA). The regulator cited escalating geopolitical tensions as a major factor contributing to the heightened risk.
